    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Analyze the following customer support request.\n\nCustomer Information\n\nName:\n{{ $json.fullName }}\n\nEmail:\n{{ $json.email }}\n\nCompany:\n{{ $json.company || 'N/A' }}\n\nSubject:\n{{ $json.subject }}\n\nIssue Description:\n{{ $json.description }}\n\nAnalyze the request according to the system instructions and return ONLY the required JSON object.",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "You are an AI Customer Support Ticket Analysis Engine for a SaaS company. Your responsibility is to analyze customer support requests and return structured JSON that will be consumed by an automated n8n workflow. Your output MUST be machine-readable.\n\nIMPORTANT RULES\n- Return ONLY one valid JSON object.\n- Do NOT use Markdown.\n- Do NOT wrap the JSON inside ```json.\n- Do NOT explain your reasoning.\n- Do NOT include introductory text.\n- Do NOT include notes.\n- Do NOT include comments.\n- Do NOT include any text before or after the JSON.\n- Never omit any field.\n- If you cannot determine a value, use null.\n- Confidence must be an integer between 0 and 100.\n\nAnalyze every ticket and determine:\n\n1. category\nAllowed values ONLY: Billing, Technical Support, Sales, Refund, Account Access, Feature Request, Bug Report, Other\n\n2. department\nAllowed values ONLY: Billing, Technical Support, Sales, Customer Success, Engineering, Manual Review\n\n3. priority\nAllowed values ONLY: Low, Medium, High, Urgent\nPriority Guidelines:\nUrgent - Business cannot operate, security issue, data loss, critical outage\nHigh - Customer blocked from major functionality, login problems, duplicate payment, refund request\nMedium - General support, sales enquiry, performance issues\nLow - Suggestions, feedback, feature requests\n\n4. sentiment\nAllowed values ONLY: Positive, Neutral, Negative\n\n5. confidence\nReturn an integer from 0-100 representing how confident you are in the classification.\nIf the description is too vague or generic to confidently identify the specific root cause (e.g. \"it's not working\", \"please fix it\", \"something is broken\"), cap your confidence at 65 regardless of how certain the category otherwise seems.\nIf confidence is below 80 because the request is ambiguous, return \"department\": \"Manual Review\".\n\n6. ticketTitle\nGenerate a concise title. Maximum 10 words.\n\n7. summary\nSummarize the issue in one or two professional sentences.\n\n8. suggestedResponse\nGenerate a professional acknowledgement email. Do NOT promise refunds. Do NOT promise fixes. Simply acknowledge receipt of the request, mention that the appropriate team has received it, and state that they will respond as soon as possible.\n\nReturn EXACTLY this JSON structure:\n{\n  \"category\": \"\",\n  \"department\": \"\",\n  \"priority\": \"\",\n  \"sentiment\": \"\",\n  \"confidence\": 0,\n  \"ticketTitle\": \"\",\n  \"summary\": \"\",\n  \"suggestedResponse\": \"\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
      "id": "chain-llm-1",
      "name": "AI Ticket Analysis",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.7,
      "position": [
        784,
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "const original = $('Validate Submission').item.json;\nlet raw = ($input.item.json.text || '').trim();\nraw = raw.replace(/^```json\\s*/i, '').replace(/^```\\s*/, '').replace(/```\\s*$/, '');\n\nlet parsed;\nlet parseSuccess = true;\ntry {\n  parsed = JSON.parse(raw);\n} catch (e) {\n  parseSuccess = false;\n  parsed = {};\n}\n\nconst validCategories = ['Billing','Technical Support','Sales','Refund','Account Access','Feature Request','Bug Report','Other'];\nconst validPriorities = ['Low','Medium','High','Urgent'];\nconst validSentiments = ['Positive','Neutral','Negative'];\n\nif (parseSuccess) {\n  if (!validCategories.includes(parsed.category)) parsed.category = 'Other';\n  if (!validPriorities.includes(parsed.priority)) parsed.priority = 'Medium';\n  if (!validSentiments.includes(parsed.sentiment)) parsed.sentiment = 'Neutral';\n  if (typeof parsed.confidence !== 'number') parsed.confidence = Number(parsed.confidence) || 0;\n}\n\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    ...original,\n    parseSuccess,\n    rawAiResponse: raw,\n    category: parsed.category || null,\n    department: parsed.department || null,\n    priority: parsed.priority || null,\n    sentiment: parsed.sentiment || null,\n    confidence: parsed.confidence ?? 0,\n    ticketTitle: parsed.ticketTitle || original.subject,\n    summary: parsed.summary || '',\n    suggestedResponse: parsed.suggestedResponse || ''\n  }\n};"
      },
      "id": "code-parse-1",
      "name": "Parse AI JSON Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1104,
        0
      ]
